    <p>
     The sign for "quit" is based on the idea of "getting 
			out" of something. The sign starts with the dominant "H" hand (think 
			of legs) inside the non-dominant "C"-hand. Then you pull the 
			"H"-hand out of the "C"-hand.
     <br/>
    </p>
    <p>
     QUIT:
     <br/>
     <img border="0" height="230" src="/images/quit.h10.jpg" width="222"/>
     <img border="0" height="230" src="/images/quit.h11.jpg" width="222"/>
     <img border="0" height="230" src="/images/quit.h12.jpg" width="222"/>
     <br/>
    </p>
    <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1"/>
    <br/>
    QUIT:  (version 2)  "get out of"
    <br/>
    Can be used for "get out of the car" or "get off of the ride" (at an amusement 
  park) or "Count me OUT!"
